	      <p>This page is available to subscribers. <a href="https://my.worldlit.org" class="pigeon-open">Click here to sign in or get access</a>.</p>
      </div>
      
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><img src="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/GivingDay25-w.jpg" data-entity-uuid="insert-image-ea17fee8-025b-47ec-8bbd-b265b4150c11" data-entity-type="file" alt="Text reads: Help WLT raise $5000 in 24 hours. #OUGivingDay | April 8, 2025" width="960" height="640" loading="lazy"><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Over the next eight days—between now and&nbsp;<a href="https://givesooner.org/campaign_search?search=33945">Giving Day</a> (April 8)—your gift will help <em>World Literature Today</em> (<em>WLT</em>) further its mission: to serve students and readers everywhere with outstanding, timely coverage of world literature and culture. For 99 years and counting, <em>WLT</em> has been a window to the world, providing what Maya Angelou once called “absolutely the most welcome reading I’ve found in years.”&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Here’s how you can help us reach our $5,000 goal:</p><ul style="list-style-type:disc;"><li><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">For a <strong>$10</strong> gift, you will receive a one-year subscription to the digital edition of <em>World Literature Today</em> magazine. (That is 66% off of our everyday digital subscription price!)</p></li><li><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">With your <strong>$25</strong> donation, in addition to a one-year digital subscription, we will send you a set of limited-edition postcards that feature quotable quotes from recent <em>WLT</em> contributors: 2024 Nobel Prize winner Han Kang, 2025 Puterbaugh Fellow Guadalupe Nettel, 2024 Neustadt Prize laureate Ananda Devi, 2023 NSK Prize winner Gene Yang, and award-winning Turkish writer Elif Shafak.</p></li><li><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">For a <strong>$50</strong> gift, WLT will donate a copy of <em>Dispatches from the Republic of Letters</em>, the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.neustadtprize.org/university-of-oklahomas-neustadt-prize-announces-its-50-year-anniversary/">50th anniversary</a> Neustadt Prize anthology, to a student, school library, or public library of your choice.</p></li><li><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">With your <strong>$100</strong> donation, you will receive a one-year subscription to the print edition of the magazine, a copy of <em>Dispatches</em>, and one of two limited-edition broadside poems by Joy Harjo (2019–2022 US Poet Laureate) or Naomi Shihab Nye (2019–2021 US Young People’s Poet Laureate and winner of the 2013 NSK Prize). One broadside features Joy’s “<a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/poetry/joy-harjos-eagle-poem-translated-arabic-ibtisam-barakat">Eagle Poem</a>” in English, Spanish, and Arabic, while the other features Naomi’s “<a href="https://www.poetryfoundation.org/poems/54296/jerusalem-56d2347ab7a20">Jerusalem</a>” poem in English, Arabic, and Hebrew.</p></li></ul><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Visit&nbsp;<a href="https://givesooner.org/campaign_search?search=33945">givesooner.org</a> to help us raise $5,000 in 24 hours! Gifts in any amount are welcome.</p><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">And to learn more about <em>WLT</em>’s $4 million endowment campaign leading up to the magazine’s centennial in 2026–2027, visit the&nbsp;<a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/donate">March to 100</a> page on the WLT website.</p><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">Questions? Please call 405-325-0317 or email&nbsp;<a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#285c4c5b5c5d4a4a68475d064d4c5d"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="2f5b4b5c5b5a4d4d6f405a014a4b5a">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>.&nbsp;</p><p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;">#OUGivingDay<br>April 8, 2025</p></div>
      <section class="field field--name-comment-node-blog-post field--type-comment field--label-hidden comment-wrapper">
  
  

  
</section>

